TRIADIC CLOSURE LICENSE (TCL)
========================================================================

Version:    1.3
Date:       2026-04-14
Supersedes: TCL v1.2 (2026-04-09), v1.1 (2026-04-07), v1.0 (2026-04-05)
History:    Full revision history preserved in git log at the
            canonical URL below. All prior versions viewable in
            git history.

            v1.3 adds no new substantive clauses and makes no
            material or textual changes to the license terms of
            v1.2. It bumps the version to mark the point at which
            the originating author formally signs the license via
            the ATTESTATION OF RELEASE block added at the end of
            this document, and to note that TCL v1.2 was tested in
            live conditions during the 2026-04-09 through
            2026-04-13 sequence of coordinated multi-channel
            attack, medical-legal pressure, and distributed-witness
            response. No clause of v1.2 required amendment under
            that test; the language held.

            v1.2 added THE WITNESS IS THE GATE clause following a
            live witness-failure case study (the framework's own
            creator overrode the witness in a two-body interaction
            and was scammed; the documented failure is the
            strongest possible evidence that the framework requires
            the gate, not just the diagnosis).

